<p><ent>Four</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Four
<hw>Four</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sum of four units;
four units or objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing four units, as 4 or
iv.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Four things of the same kind, esp. four horses;
<as>as, a chariot and <ex>four</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>All fours</b></col>. <cd>See <er>All fours</er>, in the
Vocabulary.</cd></cs></p>

